        "verdict": "needs-attention",
        "topFinding": "First deep full fan-out since 2026-06-28 (the runs between were carry-forwards); looking harder surfaced real latent issues the earlier zero-finding passes missed, not regressions (only three housekeeping commits landed since). One live runtime bug flips the verdict: all four INSERT INTO meta (key, value) statements in server.ts omit the NOT NULL updated_at column, so first-launch consent (POST /api/consent) and every app-lock write throw SQLITE_CONSTRAINT_NOTNULL 500, breaking two shipped v0.12.0 features. Second, a real Discord webhook bearer URL committed in 5b3d7cc was only untracked, never rotated or history-scrubbed, so it stays reachable in history on origin/main (private repo, so blast radius is collaborators only). All seven hard rules hold (D-006, D-003, D-001, D-004/D-007 verified live and clean), so there is no BLOCK and the core money paths are solid with 148 green API tests.",
